300.definition: Alteration confined to volumes of rocks exhibiting a foliation.

301.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a fracture, i.e. with any break/separation in a geological formation with or without relative displacement of the parts (e.g. a joint or a fault).

302.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a breccia.

303.definition: Alteration restricted to compositionally or texturally defined layers within rocks.

304.definition: Alteration that has replaced or filled in only certain portions of the rock at the scale of observation (e.g. the envelopes around veins), certain primary minerals, or pore spaces (including vesicles and interclast voids).

305.definition: Alteration characterized by the replacement of most, or all, original rock-forming minerals and obliteration of textures at the scale of observation.

306.definition: Alteration characterized by the replacement of only specific components (e.g. minerals, grains, clasts) of the original rock, with partial to complete obliteration of textures at the scale of observation.

308.definition: Alteration characterized by the replacement of only specific components (e.g. minerals, grains, clasts) of the original rock, with partial to complete obliteration of textures across the whole area of observation.

309.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a shear zone.

310.definition: Alteration spatially restricted to rocks within and/or immediately adjacent to structures such as shear zones, fault zones, veins, hydrothermal breccias, vugs or fractures.

312.definition: Alteration that occurs at or around an unconformable or disconformable contact.

313.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a vein.

314.definition: Alteration associated with small cavities in a vein or rock, usually lined with crystals of a different mineral composition from the enclosing rock.

315.definition: Alteration that can be divided spatially into several mineralogically or texturally distinct regions, with systematic variations in mineral assemblages, compositions and/or textures.
